{"title_page": "Kariya (film)", "text_new": "{{Short description|2003 gangster film by Prem}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Kariya\n| film name      = {{Film name|Kannada|\u0c95\u0cb0\u0cbf\u0caf}}\n| image          = Kariyaa.jpg\n| image_size     = 220\n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Prem (film director)|Prem]]\n| producer       = Anekal Balaraju\n| story          = Prem\n| screenplay     = Prem\n| writer         = Malavalli Saikrishna<br>{{small|(Dialogues)}}\n| starring       = [[Darshan Thoogudeep]]<br>[[Abinayasri]]\n| music          = [[Gurukiran]]\n| cinematography = M. R. Seenu\n| editing        = Srinivas P Babu\n| studio         = Santhosh Enterprises\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2003|01|03}}\n| runtime        = 144 minutes\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = Kannada\n}}\n\n'''''Kariya''''' is a [[2003 in film|2003]] Indian [[Cinema of Karnataka|Kannada]] [[gangster film]] written and directed by [[Prem (film director)|Prem]] starring [[Darshan Thoogudeep]] and [[Abinayasri]] in the lead roles. It narrates the tragic story of a homeless [[contract killer|assassin-for-hire]] Kariya who falls for Maya a well educated and rich dancer. Although she tries to convey her feelings Kariya hesitantly moves away causing her to pledge that she will only reciprocate his feelings if he proclaims his love for her. Parallelly, a few local thugs try to entrap Kariya and seek vengeance for the death of their friend.\n\nThe film received positive response from critics and audience alike and turned out to be a box office success. Kariya received acclaim for the raw depiction of crime. The film has attained a massive [[cult following]] and has been re-released more than 15 times on demand by the audience.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Darshan Thoogudeep]]\n* [[Abinayasri]]\n* Mico Nagaraj \n* Umesh Punga \n* Nanda kishore \n* Dashavara chandru \n* Nandesh\n* John \n* B. Jayashree \n* Five star Ganesh \n* Sanketh kashi\n*Real 23 Underworld Gangsters \n*\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name          = Kariya\n| released      = 27 May 2002\n| recorded      = 2002\n| genre         = [[Film Soundtrack|Feature film Soundtrack]]\n| type          = Soundtrack\n| artist        = Gurukiran\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! S. No !! Track Title !! Lyricist(s) !! Singer(s)\n|-\n| 1 || \"Hrudayada Volage\" || [[V. Nagendra Prasad]] || [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]], [[Kavita Krishnamurthy]]\n|-\n| 2 || \"Ell Ellinda\" || [[Kaviraj (lyricist)|Kaviraj]] || [[Gurukiran]], [[Anuradha Paudwal]]\n|-\n| 3 || \"Maathadu Saku\" || [[V. Nagendra Prasad]] || [[Gurukiran]]\n|-\n| 4 || \"Kenchalo Manchalo\" || [[V. Nagendra Prasad]] || [[C. Ashwath]], Gururaj Hoskote, Murali Mohan\n|-\n| 5 || \"Nannali Naanilla\" || [[Kaviraj (lyricist)|Kaviraj]] || [[Udit Narayan]], [[Shamitha Malnad|Shamitha]]\n|}\n\n== Production ==\nKariya is the second film of [[Prem (film director)|Prem]] as a director after Excuse Me. Having a gangster backdrop, director Prem and producer Anekal Balaraj bailed out 23 criminals to act in the film. Balraj tried to persuade a female mobster Mari Mutthu to act in the film. However, Mari Mutthu who was a councillor refused the offer fearing it might tarnish her reputation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.viggy.com/news/volume2/current_kariya.asp|title=23 Rowdies in Kariya|website=viggy.com|accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref> Certain scenes involving these rowdies were shot in exactly the same spot where they have killed or assaulted their targets in the past. [[Darshan Thoogudeep|Darshan]] who made his debut through the crime film [[Majestic (film)|Majestic]] was chosen to play the titular role while [[Abhinayashree|Abhirami]], daughter of actress Anuradha was signed in to play the female lead. [[Gurukiran]] has scored and composed the film's soundtrack. Cinematography was handled by Seenu.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.viggy.com/english/wings_kariya.asp|website=viggy.com|title=Darshan's Kariya to release on January 3rd|accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nKariya received an ''A certificate'' from regional office of the [[Censor Board]] at [[Bangalore]] with the certificate dated 30 December 2002.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://movies.syzygy.in/censor/kariya-celluloid|website=movies.syzygy.in|title=Kariya Censor Report|accessdate=15 February 2020}}</ref> The film was released on 3 January 2003.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://chiloka.com/movie/kariya-2003|website=chiloka.com|accessdate=16 February 2003|title=Kariya film details}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Critical Reception ===\nAccording to ''Viggy'', \"There are some catchy dialogues and comedy to make you laugh if you are freezed looking at the blood pool.\" Though they criticised the musical score by Gurukiran and wrong casting of Darshan in the lead role, the film's cinematography and Prem's direction received praise. The similarities of certain scenes with that of Om and Satya were pointed out.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.viggy.com/english/review_kariya.asp|title=Kariya review|website=viggy.com|accessdate=11 February 2020}}</ref>\n \n''Chitraloka'' criticised the film for not catering much to the women or the younger generation. But they praised Darshan's performance, Gurukiran's music and M. R. Seenu's camerawork were appreciated. The film was also lauded for its technical prowness.<ref>{{Cite web|date=3 January 2003|accessdate=11 February 2020|title=\u0c95\u0cb0\u0cbf\u0caf Review|website=chitraloka.com|url=https://www.chitraloka.com/movie-reviews/2803-kariya-review.html}}</ref>\n\n''Nettv4u'' gave the film 3.5 stars on 5 calling Kariya one of Darshan's best films which could draw more of his fans to theatres to watch the different effort. While the film received praise for its technical aspects, direction and cinematography the film was criticised for its violence.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nettv4u.com/movie-review/kannada/kariya|accessdate=11 February 2020|website=nettv4u.com|title=Kariya 2003 film review}}</ref>\n\n=== Box office ===\nKariya had a big opening. It ran for 35 to 56 days at Kapali theatre during its first release. At the end of its first run the film was declared a [[sleeper hit]]. However, due to demand by the viewers the film was released again when it turned out to be a greater success enjoying a theatrical run of more than 100 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chitraloka.com/flash-back/3153-2003-year-round-up.html|website=chitraloka.com|accessdate=15 February 2020|date=31 December 2003|title=2003 Year Round Up}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sandalwoodking.rocks/threads/darshan-thoogudeepa-challenging-star-karunada-kala-rathna-actor-producer.6461/page-7|accessdate=15 February 2020|website=sandalwoodking.rocks|title=Darshan hits and flops|first=|last=SubhashChandraGandhi|date=23 August 2016}}</ref> During its second release the film was declared a [[Blockbuster (entertainment)|Blockbuster]] completing a theatrical run of 675 days in [[Karnataka]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Darshan best films|accessdate=16 February 2020|website=celebritykick.in|url=http://celebritykick.com/kannada-actor/darshan-movies}}</ref>\n\n==Controversy==\nThere is a song in the film called \"Nee nanage sigadiddare acid hakuve\" (\"If I don't get you, I will [[Acid throwing|pour acid]] on you\").  The ''Karnataka State Commission for Women'' has asked the censor board to ban such films, claiming they encouraged crimes against women.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2003-11-27/bangalore/27190835_1_kannada-film-film-certification-film-industry | title=Women's panel sees red over violent films | newspaper=Times of India | date=27 Nov 2003}}</ref>\n\n==Legacy==\nThe sequel ''[[Kariya 2]]'' which was unrelated to 2003 film was released in 2017. However both films were produced by Anekal Balaraju.<ref>{{Cite web|date=13 October 2017|accessdate=|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/131017/kariya-2-movie-review-a-mental-suffering.html|website=deccanchronicle.com|title=Kariya 2 is a mental suffering}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Prem (director)}}\n\n[[Category:Films set in Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2003 films]]\n[[Category:2000s Kannada-language films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Gurukiran]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Indian gangster films]]\n[[Category:Indian action films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|2003 gangster film by Prem}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Kariya\n| film name      = {{Film name|Kannada|\u0c95\u0cb0\u0cbf\u0caf}}\n| image          = Kariyaa.jpg\n| image_size     = 220\n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Prem (film director)|Prem]]\n| producer       = Anekal Balaraju\n| story          = Prem\n| screenplay     = Prem\n| writer         = Malavalli Saikrishna<br>{{small|(Dialogues)}}\n| starring       = [[Darshan Thoogudeep]]<br>[[Abinayasri]]\n| music          = [[Gurukiran]]\n| cinematography = M. R. Seenu\n| editing        = Srinivas P Babu\n| studio         = Santhosh Enterprises\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2003|01|03}}\n| runtime        = 144 minutes\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = Kannada\n}}\n\n'''''Kariya''''' is a [[2003 in film|2003]] Indian [[Cinema of Karnataka|Kannada]] [[gangster film]] written and directed by [[Prem (film director)|Prem]] starring [[Darshan Thoogudeep]] and [[Abinayasri]] in the lead roles. It narrates the tragic story of a homeless [[contract killer|assassin-for-hire]] Kariya who falls for Maya a well educated and rich dancer. Although she tries to convey her feelings Kariya hesitantly moves away causing her to pledge that she will only reciprocate his feelings if he proclaims his love for her. Parallelly, a few local thugs try to entrap Kariya and seek vengeance for the death of their friend.\n\nThe film received positive response from critics and audience alike and turned out to be a box office success. Kariya received acclaim for the raw depiction of crime. The film has attained a massive [[cult following]] and has been re-released more than 15 times on demand by the audience.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Darshan Thoogudeep]]\n* [[Abinayasri]]\n* Mico Nagaraj \n* Umesh Punga \n* Nanda kishore \n* Dashavara chandru \n* Nandesh\n* John \n* B. Jayashree \n* Five star Ganesh \n* Sanketh kashi\n*Real 23 Underworld Gangsters \n*\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name          = Kariya\n| released      = 27 May 2002\n| recorded      = 2002\n| genre         = [[Film Soundtrack|Feature film Soundtrack]]\n| type          = Soundtrack\n| artist        = Gurukiran\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! S. No !! Track Title !! Lyricist(s) !! Singer(s)\n|-\n| 1 || \"Hrudayada Volage\" || [[V. Nagendra Prasad]] || [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]], [[Kavita Krishnamurthy]]\n|-\n| 2 || \"Ell Ellinda\" || [[Kaviraj (lyricist)|Kaviraj]] || [[Gurukiran]], [[Anuradha Paudwal]]\n|-\n| 3 || \"Maathadu Saku\" || [[V. Nagendra Prasad]] || [[Gurukiran]]\n|-\n| 4 || \"Kenchalo Manchalo\" || [[V. Nagendra Prasad]] || [[C. Ashwath]], Gururaj Hoskote, Murali Mohan\n|-\n| 5 || \"Nannali Naanilla\" || [[Kaviraj (lyricist)|Kaviraj]] || [[Udit Narayan]], [[Shamitha Malnad|Shamitha]]\n|}\n\n== Production ==\nKariya is the second film of [[Prem (film director)|Prem]] as a director after Excuse Me. Having a gangster backdrop, director Prem and producer Anekal Balaraj bailed out 23 criminals to act in the film. Balraj tried to persuade a female mobster Mari Mutthu to act in the film. However, Mari Mutthu who was a councillor refused the offer fearing it might tarnish her reputation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.viggy.com/news/volume2/current_kariya.asp|title=23 Rowdies in Kariya|website=viggy.com|accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref> Certain scenes involving these rowdies were shot in